pay attention to you,

15:09.532 --> 15:13.327
my sweet little father-loving
pile of forgiveness.

15:13.411 --> 15:15.663
- Yes.
- [ Knocking ]

15:17.289 --> 15:20.000
Can Lisa come out
with her hands up?

15:21.710 --> 15:26.215
Chief Wiggum, my daughter is
innocent until proven guilty.

15:26.298 --> 15:28.551
[Tires Squealing]

15:29.552 --> 15:31.512
Would an innocent person flee?

15:32.763 --> 15:34.974
No, really. Tell me.
I honestly don't know.

15:35.057 --> 15:37.476
Chief, no.
Even I knew that.

15:37.560 --> 15:40.563
Yeah. Yeah.
I'm not- I'm not good.

15:42.690 --> 15:45.985
[Sirens Wailing]

15:49.363 --> 15:51.240
[ Chuckles ]
They're trapped.

15:55.870 --> 15:58.164
Oh, damn it!

15:59.206 --> 16:01.792
[ Groans ]
I can't stop worrying...

16:01.876 --> 16:03.711
about Homer and Lisa.

16:03.794 --> 16:07.006
Aw, Mom.
This'll take your mind off them.

16:07.089 --> 16:08.799
[Grunts]

16:08.883 --> 16:11.844
Oh, thank you, sweetie.

16:11.927 --> 16:14.638
♪♪ [ Humming]
[ Bowl Smashes ]

16:14.722 --> 16:18.058
<i>[ Man On Radio] Police are looking
for a bald man in blue pants...</i>

16:18.142 --> 16:20.478
<i>and a fair-haired girl
in a red lampshade.</i>

16:20.561 --> 16:23.814
Blackening our hair
was a great idea, Dad.

16:23.898 --> 16:26.484
I look just like
a Powerpuff Girl.

16:26.567 --> 16:28.944
I look just like Elvis.

16:29.904 --> 16:30.905
[ Groans ]

16:34.283 --> 16:38.329
- Names, please?
- Lady Penelope Ariel Ponyweather.

16:38.412 --> 16:40.414
Uh, Rock Strongo.

16:40.498 --> 16:43.459
- Your real name.
- Uh,

16:43.542 --> 16:45.628
- Lance Uppercut.
- Thank you.

16:45.711 --> 16:47.171
Sign here, Mr. Uppercut.

16:47.254 --> 16:49.757
Let me just
put on my glasses.

16:56.096 --> 16:58.891
You're charging
how much for a room?

16:58.974 --> 17:00.476
[ Phone Ringing]

17:00.559 --> 17:04.355
<i>Hello? [ Homer, Modified Voice ]
Hello- Th/ls 11s a phone survey.</i>

17:04.438 --> 17:06.982
If the election
were held today,

17:07.066 --> 17:10.361
would you vote for
the cops are there,

17:10.444 --> 17:13.030
or you're free to talk?

17:13.113 --> 17:14.823
Uh,

17:14.906 --> 17:16.492
And I'd like to add...

17:16.575 --> 17:19.619
that Proposition
“Hug Lisa For Me”...

17:19.703 --> 17:21.204
has my full support.

17:21.288 --> 17:22.998
[ Normal Voice ] No, Marge.
You're not gettin' it.

17:23.082 --> 17:24.833
It's me, Homer- Simpson.

17:24.916 --> 17:27.252
[ Nervous Chuckle]
We got a location, Chief.

17:27.336 --> 17:30.923
Good work, Lou.
We'll leave right after dinner.

17:31.799 --> 17:34.301
Lisa, this is from your morn.

17:34.385 --> 17:35.553
[Grunts]

17:35.636 --> 17:38.222
Aw. Life on the lam
is really hard.

17:38.305 --> 17:40.140
But at least
it's with you, Dad.

17:40.224 --> 17:42.726
I feel terrible
for putting you through this,

17:42.810 --> 17:44.645
after what a wonderful father
you've been.

17:46.564 --> 17:49.400
Oh. Lisa, I can't
lie to you any longer.

17:49.483 --> 17:51.193
This is all my fault.

17:51.277 --> 17:53.237
I'm the worst dad
in the world.

17:53.320 --> 17:54.655
What? Why?

17:54.738 --> 17:58.158
The man who framed you
is a crooked detective, who I hired.

17:58.242 --> 17:59.827
Why did you do that?

17:59.910 --> 18:03.205
To find out everything about you
so I'd seem like a good father.

18:03.289 --> 18:04.957
How could you?

18:05.040 --> 18:08.586
Well, all the childless drunks at Moe's
thought it was a great idea.

18:08.669 --> 18:10.963
Let's just get some sleep.

18:19.597 --> 18:22.725
All right, Simpsons, the jig is up.
We know you're in there.

18:22.808 --> 18:25.603
[ Homer] Okay. I'm coming
right out the door.

18:25.686 --> 18:28.814
Damn it! These windows are
so hard to squeeze through.

18:28.897 --> 18:30.482
[ Homer Grunts]

18:37.281 --> 18:41.285
Cheer up, honey. We're living an
all-natural existence, the kind you like.

18:41.368 --> 18:42.870
Ooh, a trash can.

18:42.953 --> 18:44.955
We'll find breakfast in here.

18:45.039 --> 18:46.707
I don't want to eat
from the trash.

18:46.790 --> 18:48.292
Oh, a banana!

18:50.169 --> 18:53.547
[ Mutters ]
It's full of cigarette butts.

18:53.631 --> 18:55.132
So is this one.

18:55.215 --> 18:57.217
They must've come
from over there.

19:03.932 --> 19:05.434
Those are the test animals.

19:05.517 --> 19:08.312
The detective must've
sold them to the circus!

19:08.395 --> 19:12.316
We'll just tell the police. And then I'm
back to being plain old Rock Strongo.

19:12.399 --> 19:15.569
You're not telling
nobody nothing.

19:15.653 --> 19:19.323
Make one move and you'll get
a belly full of the Flying Giuseppe.

19:19.406 --> 19:21.408
How you doin'?

19:21.492 --> 19:24.536
Dexter Colt, the man
who framed my daughter!

19:24.620 --> 19:26.497
You should've paid
the expenses.

19:26.580 --> 19:28.582
In retrospect, yes!

19:30.542 --> 19:31.585
[ Gasps ]

19:39.343 --> 19:40.844
[Grunts]

19:40.928 --> 19:42.971
Ooh, I think
that fixed my back.

19:43.055 --> 19:45.432
Oh. Oh, no, no. It's much worse.
[ Bones Cracking ]

19:46.600 --> 19:48.435
[Gasping, Grunting]

19:49.645 --> 19:51.647
<i>I'll</i> just hide here.
[Gasps]

19:52.731 --> 19:55.067
[Shrieks, Whimpers]

19:55.150 --> 19:56.610
[ Electricity Crackling ]

20:00.656 --> 20:02.866
[ Cackling ]
Now what are you gonna do?

20:02.950 --> 20:04.660
You can't shoot all of us.

20:04.743 --> 20:05.744
Damn it!

20:07.621 --> 20:10.541
You know, Simpson, from the
moment you walked into my office,

20:10.624 --> 20:13.502
I had a feeling I'd kill you
in a hall of mirrors.

20:13.585 --> 20:15.212
Dad? Are you in here?

20:15.295 --> 20:16.755
How did she find us?

20:16.839 --> 20:18.632
Oh, Lisa has excellent hearing.

20:18.716 --> 20:23.137
Once when she was three, I was quietly
sobbing in the closet, and she found me.

20:23.220 --> 20:26.223
Oh, Dad, you do remember
something about me.

20:26.306 --> 20:29.810
Perhaps you also remember
this laser Bart gave me earlier.

20:29.893 --> 20:32.229
- [Zapping]
- [ Grunting]

20:32.312 --> 20:33.814
I can't see!

20:34.732 --> 20:36.817
How ironic.

20:36.900 --> 20:41.655
Now he's blind, after a life
of enjoying being able to see.

20:44.616 --> 20:46.410
Well, it wasn't easy, honey.

20:46.493 --> 20:48.328
But I'm glad
you love me again.

20:48.412 --> 20:51.999
Yeah. But what's gonna happen to
the animals? Don't worry, honey.

20:52.082 --> 20:54.209
I released them all
into the wild.

20:54.293 --> 20:56.503
[ Monkeys Chittering ]
[ Pig Squealing]

20:56.587 --> 20:59.798
Cletus, if I find pig lipstick
on your collar again,

20:59.882 --> 21:02.384
I'm not gonna let you
sleep in the sty no more.

21:02.468 --> 21:04.011
Duly noted.

21:32.706 --> 21:34.833
[Bart] Hey, Dad. Will you
read me a bedtime story?

21:34.917 --> 21:36.460
[ Homer]
Why certainly, Son.

21:36.543 --> 21:38.962
Just hand me
that book you got there.

21:39.046 --> 21:41.465
[ Book: Male Voice]
Unauthorized user! Access denied!

21:41.548 --> 21:43.008
[ Electricity Crackling ]
[ Homer Shouting ]

21:43.091 --> 21:46.053
[ Bart Laughing]
[ Homer Shrieks]

21:49.431 --> 21:51.391
Shh! [Murmuring]

21:56.396 --> 21:57.397
English - US - PSDH
